The paper proposes an approach for activity detection in video using machine learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves optimization techniques for solving the maximum-weight connected subgraph problem, which could be categorized under multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves search strategies for detecting activities in untrimmed videos, which could be categorized under information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
